    Muscat begins talks in Libya by di-ve.com - Local News -- 06 October 2008 -- 19:05CEST The Leader of the Opposition Joseph Muscat today began a visit of Libya. In his first meetings, Dr Muscat met the Secretary for Foreign Affairs Suleiman el Shahoumi and the Speaker of the General Congress of the People, Muftah Khaiba. The main subjects under discussion were energy and the international price of oil. Accompanying Dr Muscat on his visit are Dr Alex Sciberras Trigona and Mr Keith Schembri. Comments (0) 